<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-07-22.3.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa0722.htm#2">Drug Misuse</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-07-22.3.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80267" speakername="Mary Scanlon (Highlands and Islands) (Con)" spid="S2W-17718" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa0722.htm#2">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive how many methadone-related drug deaths have been recorded in each of the last three years.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/2005-07-22.3.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80062" speakername="George Lyon" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-05/wa0722.htm#2">

  <p>There were 69 methadone-related drug deaths in Scotland in 2001, 98 in 2002, and 87 in 2003. The figure for 2004 will be published on 31 August 2005 in the General Register Office for Scotland&rsquo;s annual paper on drug-related deaths.</p>

</reply>


